A MAN has been nabbed for offering cops a R5000 tjotjo. This comes after the Ekurhuleni District's crime intelligence, trio task team, Tembisa tracing team and highway patrol unit acted on a tip-off about a suspiciously marked South African Police Service (SAPS) vehicle in the Rabie Ridge area at around 1pm on Tuesday, 27 February. Information was followed and a Mazda BT50 bakkie resembling an SAPS provincial head office vehicle was stopped while driving out of a plot on Modderfontein Road in Midrand. ALSO READ:Â Madala shot dead ko skolong! The driver managed to flee the scene but he was pursued and apprehended. Preliminary investigations revealed that the vehicle was stolen in Bedfordview in December 2022. It is believed that the vehicle was being used to commit truck hijackings. While the police were busy at the crime scene, a man arrived and requested the cops to release the suspect. He offered them a R5000 tjotjo. The 46-year-old was immediately arrested for bribery. The suspects will appear in court soon.